==English==
===Etymology===
Arabic from Persian ''tāj'': "crown".

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɑːdʒ|-ɑːdʒ]]

===Noun===
'''taj'''
#A tall [[brimless]] hat, usually [[conical]] or [[curve]]d on top, worn in [[Muslim]] countries as a sign of [[distinction]] and [[prestige]].
#''(Historical)'' A [[crown]] worn by Indian [[prince]]s as a sign of high [[rank]].
